From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Paul Philippov <paul@themactep.com>
Date: Sat, 12 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] mips: guard _ABI64 with defined() in bits/wordsize.h

_ABI64 is defined in <sgidefs.h> which is not guaranteed to be included
before <bits/wordsize.h>.  Using _ABI64 without a defined() guard triggers
-Wundef warnings:

  warning: '_ABI64' is not defined, evaluates to '0'

The comparison is functionally correct (it evaluates to false on mips32),
but the warning is noisy.  Wrap it in defined() to silence the warning
regardless of include order.

Signed-off-by: Paul Philippov <paul@themactep.com>
---
 libc/sysdeps/linux/mips/bits/wordsize.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/libc/sysdeps/linux/mips/bits/wordsize.h b/libc/sysdeps/linux/mips/bits/wordsize.h
--- a/libc/sysdeps/linux/mips/bits/wordsize.h
+++ b/libc/sysdeps/linux/mips/bits/wordsize.h
@@ -16,6 +16,6 @@
    <http://www.gnu.org/licenses/>.  */
 
 #define __WORDSIZE	_MIPS_SZPTR
-#if _MIPS_SIM == _ABI64
+#if defined(_ABI64) && _MIPS_SIM == _ABI64
 # define __WORDSIZE_TIME64_COMPAT32 1
 #endif
